revision.text:
An '''adparticle''' is an [[atom]], [[molecule]], or cluster of atoms or molecules that lies on a crystal surface.  The term is used in [[surface chemistry]].  The word is a contraction of "[[adsorption|adsorbed]] particle".  An adparticle that is a single atom may be referred to as an "[[adatom]]".

[[Category:Surface science]]


